WEBVTT

00:02.963 --> 00:04.999
(violin music playing)

00:06.433 --> 00:08.469
(indistinct chatter)

00:08.502 --> 00:10.638
DENNIS:
Frank, would you like
another buttered nipple?

00:11.438 --> 00:14.542
No. The cream
is making me gassy.

00:14.575 --> 00:17.077
-Yeah, well, you have had
four of them.
-Yeah.

00:17.111 --> 00:19.013
-(both laugh)
-You know, we could order you

00:19.046 --> 00:20.815
something that's a little bit
easier on the pipes.

00:20.848 --> 00:22.416
-DENNIS: Yeah.
-You know,
I know what you're doing.

00:22.449 --> 00:23.951
This is your annual

00:23.984 --> 00:26.520
"take me out and see
if you can talk me into

00:26.554 --> 00:27.855
giving you more of my money."

00:27.888 --> 00:29.790
-Oh, stop.
-Uh-- Is he talking to us?

00:29.824 --> 00:31.792
-Give me money. (laughs)
-We would never. (laughs)

00:31.826 --> 00:33.828
-(grunts)
-DEE: And we just want you
to have a fun night.

00:33.861 --> 00:34.829
DENNIS:
Yeah.

00:34.862 --> 00:35.996
Oh. (laughs)

00:36.030 --> 00:37.865
(groans)

00:37.898 --> 00:40.000
-Yeah, get that.
-What you working on there, bud?

00:40.034 --> 00:41.936
I brought my own can
of anchovies

00:41.969 --> 00:44.405
because the fish in this place
is not salty enough.

00:44.438 --> 00:46.540
-Mm, that's...
-I agree.

00:46.574 --> 00:47.675
-Got no taste.
-DENNIS and DEE: Yeah.

00:47.708 --> 00:49.410
Yeah, no, I-I hear you.

00:49.443 --> 00:51.011
It's, uh, it's not salty enough.

00:51.045 --> 00:53.647
I want to point something out
here to you, Frank.

00:53.681 --> 00:55.950
I think we do a pretty good job

00:55.983 --> 00:57.418
of pretending like
you're not an animal.

00:57.451 --> 00:58.686
(laughs)

00:58.719 --> 00:59.620
Is that thing loaded,
by the way?

00:59.653 --> 01:00.921
Nah, it's not loaded.

01:00.955 --> 01:03.724
-(Dee sighs)
-And get off my back,

01:03.757 --> 01:04.758
huh?

01:04.792 --> 01:06.460
-Hey. Absolutely.
-Yup.

01:06.494 --> 01:07.661
You got it. (laughs)

01:07.695 --> 01:08.863
Got no intention to be

01:08.896 --> 01:10.598
-riding on your back, pal.
-No.

01:10.631 --> 01:11.966
DENNIS:
We like you
just the way you are.

01:11.999 --> 01:14.001
-Mm. Mm-hmm.
-And I think that, you know,

01:14.034 --> 01:17.004
maybe, just possibly, that
entitles us to a little taste

01:17.037 --> 01:18.806
-of your fortune after you die?
-Oh.

01:18.839 --> 01:19.874
-You know what I mean? I-I...
-Oh.

01:19.907 --> 01:21.475
I want to tell you something,

01:21.509 --> 01:23.944
I am not intending on dying
anytime soon,

01:23.978 --> 01:25.913
so don't waste your breath.

01:26.680 --> 01:28.782
-(grunts)
-(sighs)
-You know what? Screw this.

01:28.816 --> 01:30.484
-Okay.
-I... Dee, I told you
this was a mistake.

01:30.518 --> 01:31.786
-No, I know, I know.
-I-- You know what? I'm out

01:31.819 --> 01:32.987
-of here.
-Couple of vultures

01:33.020 --> 01:34.522
picking at my carcass.

01:34.555 --> 01:35.890
-Uh-huh.
-You know, I am in the prime

01:35.923 --> 01:37.391
-of my life.
-Yeah.

01:37.424 --> 01:39.460
I mean, if you think
that you can...

01:39.493 --> 01:41.796
-(gunshot)
-(Dennis and Dee scream)

01:41.829 --> 01:43.297
-DENNIS: You shot us!
-(patrons murmuring)

01:43.330 --> 01:44.465
You shot us!
I got shot in the face!

01:44.498 --> 01:45.933
You said there were no bullets!

01:45.966 --> 01:48.836
Okay, so it was loaded.
My mistake.

01:48.869 --> 01:50.471
Oh, don't be so dramatic.

01:50.504 --> 01:51.906
I just nicked you.

01:51.939 --> 01:54.375
It's not like anybody's
in any real danger.

01:55.342 --> 01:57.378
♪ ♪

02:19.567 --> 02:21.368
I'm saying, don't shoot
the whole balloon down, right?

02:21.402 --> 02:22.803
-Like, you-you pull it down...
-Frank shot us.

02:22.837 --> 02:24.772
He shot us in the face.
We barely survived.

02:24.805 --> 02:26.006
Awesome.

02:26.040 --> 02:27.741
-Wha...
-Uh, no, not awesome.

02:27.775 --> 02:30.044
Oh, sorry.
You came in all excited.

02:30.077 --> 02:31.679
I thought you were bragging.

02:31.712 --> 02:33.414
I was picking up
on an excited energy, for sure.

02:33.447 --> 02:34.915
Getting shot in the face
and surviving is pretty cool.

02:34.949 --> 02:35.916
Yeah.

02:35.950 --> 02:37.618
This is insane.

02:37.651 --> 02:38.986
Listen, we got to get his gun
away from him, okay?

02:39.019 --> 02:40.521
I-I don't even care
about the money anymore.

02:40.554 --> 02:41.755
Oh, yeah, no, no, neither do I.

02:41.789 --> 02:42.790
I don't give a shit
about the money.

02:42.823 --> 02:44.592
I mean, the man is a maniac,

02:44.625 --> 02:45.993
and he's gonna wind up shooting
everyone in this bar.

02:46.026 --> 02:47.528
Oh, yeah. I do care
about the money, though.

02:47.561 --> 02:49.663
-Yeah, no, so do I. Absolutely.
-Yeah.

02:49.697 --> 02:50.998
-It's the only thing I care
about. Are you kidding me?
-Yeah. Yeah.

02:51.031 --> 02:52.733
Come on. You know
what I'm worried about?

02:52.766 --> 02:54.001
I'm worried he's gonna
kill himself with that gun

02:54.034 --> 02:55.035
before he gets
old and senile enough

02:55.069 --> 02:56.637
to rewrite us into the will.

02:56.670 --> 02:58.005
That's it. That's it.
We need him to live

02:58.038 --> 02:59.640
long enough
so he can become fully demented.

02:59.673 --> 03:00.641
-Mm-hmm.
-CHARLIE: I know, but, guys,

03:00.674 --> 03:01.809
I'm picking up, like,

03:01.842 --> 03:03.377
a super stressed-out vibe
from you,

03:03.410 --> 03:05.646
and it's really important
to remember, like,

03:05.679 --> 03:08.082
you know,
money isn't everything.

03:08.115 --> 03:10.084
Yeah, of course
you don't care, Charlie,

03:10.117 --> 03:12.019
because your dad didn't have
anything to pass down to you.

03:12.052 --> 03:14.989
No, that's true,
but my mom does. Yeah.

03:15.022 --> 03:17.925
On my mom's family side, I got a
huge inheritance coming my way.

03:17.958 --> 03:20.361
Wait, what?

03:20.394 --> 03:22.363
H-How did I not know this?
You're gonna be rich?

03:22.396 --> 03:24.465
Yeah. Totally. Yeah.

03:24.498 --> 03:27.768
Well, uh,
rich in history and legacy

03:27.802 --> 03:29.937
and, uh... (clear throat)
...teeth, of course.

03:29.970 --> 03:31.739
Teeth?

03:31.772 --> 03:34.375
Yeah. It's a pretty sweet deal,
actually, you know.

03:34.408 --> 03:36.076
Everyone on my mom's side
of the family,

03:36.110 --> 03:38.813
going back to the Niña
and the-the Pinta

03:38.846 --> 03:40.614
and the, uh, Santa Margherita,

03:40.648 --> 03:43.017
um, they've all been putting
their teeth into a jar

03:43.050 --> 03:44.485
-when they die.
-Mm-hmm.

03:44.518 --> 03:46.620
And, uh, when I turn 40,

03:46.654 --> 03:47.988
that sweet little piece

03:48.022 --> 03:49.590
of history's coming my way.

03:49.623 --> 03:50.858
Just stop. Okay, Dee,

03:50.891 --> 03:51.926
we need to get that gun
away from Frank.

03:51.959 --> 03:53.627
Whoa-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh.

03:53.661 --> 03:55.362
You don't do something
like that.

03:55.396 --> 03:57.331
You know, because, like,
Frank's gun is a big piece

03:57.364 --> 03:58.666
of who he is, right?

03:58.699 --> 04:00.334
That's his legacy.
That's his history.

04:00.367 --> 04:02.770
That's like, that's like
my jar of teeth, right?

04:02.803 --> 04:04.772
I don't want that taken away
from me when I get old.

04:04.805 --> 04:06.373
What are you talking about?

04:06.407 --> 04:09.343
Charlie, I got some
bad news for you, bud.

04:09.376 --> 04:10.377
What?

04:10.411 --> 04:12.847
You turned 40 a long time ago.

04:15.416 --> 04:17.351
Yo. Hey, Ma, how you doing?

04:17.384 --> 04:19.386
-Hi, Mom.
-Oh, hi, boys.

04:19.420 --> 04:21.055
-What brings you by?
-Yeah, uh,

04:21.088 --> 04:23.591
hey, I want to show Mac
that jar of family teeth we got.

04:23.624 --> 04:24.792
Oh.

04:24.825 --> 04:26.360
-Y-You-you do?
-CHARLIE: Yeah.

04:26.393 --> 04:27.895
Hey, Ma, did you realize
I was over 40?

04:27.928 --> 04:29.897
(gasps) You are?

04:29.930 --> 04:31.999
Yeah, turns out. Yeah, I figured
you probably forgot, too,

04:32.032 --> 04:33.534
or something, but, um, yeah,

04:33.567 --> 04:34.802
can I get that jar of teeth
now, please?

04:34.835 --> 04:36.871
Oh, okay, I-I'll go
look for them.

04:36.904 --> 04:39.039
Okay, yeah, good.
Go-go get my teeth, please.

04:39.073 --> 04:40.374
Cool. Hey, Mom,

04:40.407 --> 04:41.509
since we're here, um,

04:41.542 --> 04:42.610
do we have any kind of, like,

04:42.643 --> 04:43.944
family heirlooms or anything?

04:43.978 --> 04:45.746
No.

04:45.779 --> 04:47.781
(sighs) Like, anything of value

04:47.815 --> 04:49.650
that our family owned
at some point?

04:49.683 --> 04:51.485
No.

04:51.519 --> 04:54.054
Hm. Okay, what if it's just,
like, sentimental?

04:54.088 --> 04:55.723
Just, like,
proof that we existed?

04:55.756 --> 04:57.758
Nope.

04:57.792 --> 04:59.026
Wait, what about those letters?

04:59.059 --> 05:00.528
Weren't there
some kind of letters

05:00.561 --> 05:01.462
that my grandfather
wrote to my dad

05:01.495 --> 05:02.429
during World War II?

05:03.430 --> 05:04.899
Yeah.

05:04.932 --> 05:06.600
Those letters exist?
Well, well, who's got them?

05:06.634 --> 05:08.536
Donald.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.938
-Donald? Donald who?
-Oh...

05:10.971 --> 05:13.040
Duck.

05:13.073 --> 05:15.042
(laughs) Yeah.

05:15.075 --> 05:17.044
Donald... Donald Duck?
What's she talking about?

05:17.077 --> 05:19.013
Yeah, my mom's making a joke.
She's-she's really funny.

05:19.046 --> 05:20.881
She's got a great sense
of humor. Right, Mom?

05:20.915 --> 05:22.883
Yeah.

05:22.917 --> 05:24.652
Yeah. She's talking
about my Uncle Donald.

05:24.685 --> 05:26.620
Huh. I didn't even know
you had an uncle Donald.

05:26.654 --> 05:28.022
Yeah, yeah,
that's my dad's brother.

05:28.055 --> 05:29.857
Donald McDonald?

05:29.890 --> 05:30.925
Yeah.

05:30.958 --> 05:32.660
Ronald McDonald.

05:32.693 --> 05:35.029
Donald McDonald. Wow.

05:35.062 --> 05:37.331
Your dad really scored with
the name Luther, I guess, huh?

05:37.364 --> 05:38.399
(Bonnie screams)

05:38.432 --> 05:40.634
Mom? What happened?

05:40.668 --> 05:42.336
-MAC: Oh, shit.
-(muffled whimper)

05:42.369 --> 05:43.737
Did she try to pull out
her own teeth?

05:43.771 --> 05:44.939
Did you just try to pull out
your own teeth?

05:44.972 --> 05:47.007
-Mm-mm.
-She clearly did.

05:47.041 --> 05:48.742
-I can see the pliers.
-We can see the pliers, Mom.

05:49.810 --> 05:51.779
-Ah! Ugh!
-Oh!

05:51.812 --> 05:54.381
-I'm so sorry.
-CHARLIE: Mom.

05:54.415 --> 05:56.750
Oh, my God. Why did you do that?

05:56.784 --> 05:59.320
I didn't have the heart
to-to tell you,

05:59.353 --> 06:02.389
I gave away the jar. (crying)

06:02.423 --> 06:04.625
You gave away the jar of teeth?
To who?

06:04.658 --> 06:05.926
Your sisters.

06:05.960 --> 06:07.728
To my sisters?

06:07.761 --> 06:10.030
Those ungrateful bitches.
What the hell, Mom?

06:10.064 --> 06:11.732
They don't even live
in Philly anymore.

06:11.765 --> 06:12.933
They moved all the way
up to northern New Jersey.

06:12.967 --> 06:14.802
They're terrible to you.

06:14.835 --> 06:16.403
I'm the one who stayed. I'm
the one who takes care of you.

06:16.437 --> 06:17.638
How could you do that?

06:17.671 --> 06:19.006
(screaming)

06:19.039 --> 06:21.342
-Now she's screaming.
-This is crazy.

06:21.375 --> 06:22.943
Now she's screaming.
Now she's screaming.

06:22.977 --> 06:24.612
-Well, you yelled at her.
-Now Mom's screaming.

06:24.645 --> 06:26.013
Now Mom's screaming.

06:26.046 --> 06:28.482
Ah, I can't believe
you did this.

06:28.516 --> 06:30.518
-Why are you yelling at her?
I don't know...
-She gave it away to my sisters.

06:30.551 --> 06:31.919
They're the worst people
on the planet.

06:31.952 --> 06:32.920
I didn't even remember
that you had sisters.

06:32.953 --> 06:34.622
All right. Okay, okay.

06:34.655 --> 06:36.390
Look, we're just gonna have
to go and get them.

06:36.423 --> 06:37.925
I think she's having
a stroke, dude.

06:37.958 --> 06:39.860
We're just gonna have
to get in the car right now

06:39.894 --> 06:41.028
-and go get them. Come on, man.
-We should go to the hospital.

06:41.061 --> 06:42.730
Let's get in the car. Let's go.

06:42.763 --> 06:44.465
Mrs. Mac, we're taking your car.
Mom, just calm down.

06:44.498 --> 06:46.467
It's okay, okay? I'm not mad
at you. It's fine, okay?

06:46.500 --> 06:48.068
-I love you.
-Breathe through your,
breathe through your nose.

06:48.102 --> 06:49.670
-I love you, too.
I love you, too.
-This is fucking insane.

06:49.703 --> 06:51.505
I made a mistake.

06:51.539 --> 06:53.674
You did make a mistake.
You did make this... All right.

06:53.707 --> 06:55.342
Christ, let's get her
cleaned up. All right.

06:55.376 --> 06:56.343
I didn't mean to upset you.

06:56.377 --> 06:58.312
(Frank grunting)

06:59.547 --> 07:01.081
Frank, um,

07:01.115 --> 07:02.750
could you stop scratching
yourself with the gun, please?

07:02.783 --> 07:04.452
-I'm itchy, I'm itchy.
-I-I bet.

07:04.485 --> 07:05.753
Probably from rolling around
in the grass

07:05.786 --> 07:06.987
outside of your apartment.

07:07.021 --> 07:08.589
No, I was rolling around
in the grass

07:08.622 --> 07:09.723
because I was itchy.

07:09.757 --> 07:10.991
The itch came first.

07:11.025 --> 07:12.660
Okay, well, why don't you
hand me the gun,

07:12.693 --> 07:13.727
-and I'll scratch you
with my fingers.
-Yeah.

07:13.761 --> 07:15.396
I'm not gonna hand you my gun,

07:15.429 --> 07:16.597
but I'll let you scratch.
You want to scratch me?

07:16.630 --> 07:19.066
-Go on. (grunts) Yeah.
-Okay.

07:19.099 --> 07:20.768
-All right.
-Scratch me. See.

07:20.801 --> 07:22.870
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Do it down by the neck.

07:22.903 --> 07:24.672
-Frank, I...
-FRANK: The back of the neck.
The back of the neck.

07:24.705 --> 07:25.606
-Okay, but I just don't want
to get shot again, is all.

07:25.639 --> 07:27.007
The gun's not loaded.

07:27.041 --> 07:28.609
Yeah, that's what you said
last time, Frank.

07:28.642 --> 07:30.511
FRANK:
(grunts) I got to take a piss.

07:30.544 --> 07:31.846
-Pull over.
-DENNIS: All right.

07:36.417 --> 07:38.352
(grunting)

07:38.385 --> 07:39.453
Okay.

07:39.487 --> 07:40.988
-(grunting)
-Goddamn it.

07:41.021 --> 07:42.590
This is not working.

07:42.623 --> 07:44.024
Should we just attack him
and take it?

07:44.058 --> 07:45.993
What? No.

07:46.026 --> 07:47.761
He'd mow us down like Scarface.
We can't come at him like that.

07:47.795 --> 07:49.864
-We'll spook him.
-Yeah.

07:49.897 --> 07:51.398
You know what?
He needs to be lulled

07:51.432 --> 07:52.933
into a false sense of security.

07:52.967 --> 07:54.768
You don't tell a dog
you're taking him to a vet

07:54.802 --> 07:55.870
to put him down.

07:55.903 --> 07:57.438
Right.

07:58.205 --> 08:01.075
You give
that dog
the best day of his life,

08:01.108 --> 08:03.777
and then you turn out the lights
when he least suspects it.

08:03.811 --> 08:05.946
-(laughs)
-Okay.

08:05.980 --> 08:07.548
Okay. Oh...

08:07.581 --> 08:09.617
Ooh.

08:09.650 --> 08:11.986
Ooh, that was a long wait.

08:12.019 --> 08:13.954
-Woo.
-Wow.

08:19.794 --> 08:21.328
♪ Just can't wait... ♪

08:21.362 --> 08:22.863
Why is your mom driving
my mom's car?

08:22.897 --> 08:24.465
I don't know. Dude, they got
some weird arrangement

08:24.498 --> 08:26.734
worked out so your mom
can focus on smoking.

08:26.767 --> 08:28.636
Speaking of, I'm getting
choked to death back here.

08:28.669 --> 08:30.771
Mrs. Mac, do you mind, like,
cracking a window or something?

08:30.805 --> 08:32.506
No.

08:32.540 --> 08:34.375
Why not? I mean, it's ridiculous
to just sit in the smoke.

08:34.408 --> 08:37.912
'Cause it's too drafty.
It's unhealthy.

08:37.945 --> 08:39.613
-Right.
-Unheal-- What?

08:39.647 --> 08:41.382
Sorry, my mom's on
a new health kick. (laughs)

08:41.415 --> 08:43.350
Hey, Mom, it's working.
You look great.

08:43.384 --> 08:44.852
Shut up.

08:44.885 --> 08:46.654
CHARLIE:
Can we, like speed up
or something?

08:46.687 --> 08:48.722
Another car just passed us.
Mom, that's, like, the 50th car.

08:48.756 --> 08:50.024
Why are you going so slow?

08:50.057 --> 08:51.859
Well, highways are scary.

08:51.892 --> 08:53.594
You're going 35.

08:53.627 --> 08:54.628
-I can see you're going 35.
-But-- And everybody's

08:54.662 --> 08:55.763
just in such a hurry.

08:55.796 --> 08:57.465
No, it's just the normal--

08:57.498 --> 08:59.033
It's the speed that people go
on the highway.

08:59.066 --> 09:00.601
Okay, maybe I should drive.
Mom, can I drive your car?

09:00.634 --> 09:01.936
-Can Mac drive?
-No.

09:01.969 --> 09:04.605
Ugh, this is my worst
nightmare, man.

09:04.638 --> 09:06.373
This is absolutely terrible.
How much further?

09:06.407 --> 09:07.875
Anyone know? Mac?

09:07.908 --> 09:09.910
How much further? Mac?

09:09.944 --> 09:11.779
Mac? Hello?

09:11.812 --> 09:15.082
(whispering): My mom's finger
is up, which means "no talking".

09:15.115 --> 09:16.784
She's annoyed. It's best if we

09:16.817 --> 09:18.986
just keep it down
until the finger goes down,

09:19.019 --> 09:21.489
otherwise, she might burn us
with the cigarette lighter.

09:21.522 --> 09:23.657
(whispers):
This is my worst nightmare

09:23.691 --> 09:24.959
in my entire life.

09:25.893 --> 09:27.995
(normal volume):
Okay, finger's down. Um, great.

09:28.028 --> 09:29.864
Uh, okay, Mrs. Kelly,
you're gonna want to stay

09:29.897 --> 09:32.366
on the Jersey Turnpike
until you hit 287.

09:32.399 --> 09:34.502
You want to take 287
towards Hamburg.

09:34.535 --> 09:36.504
Mm, no. That--
No, you just stay on the 206

09:36.537 --> 09:37.505
the whole way up.

09:37.538 --> 09:38.806
No, no, we're gonna,

09:38.839 --> 09:39.907
we're gonna hit Hamburg
on the way.

09:39.940 --> 09:41.041
Why are we going to Hamburg?

09:41.075 --> 09:42.743
We're gonna visit
my Uncle Donald.

09:42.776 --> 09:45.546
-Donald McDonald
of Hamburger, New Jersey?
-Hamburg.

09:45.579 --> 09:47.515
A bunch of old letters that
weren't even written to you?

09:47.548 --> 09:49.049
That's not a legacy, it's
a bunch of meaningless shit.

09:49.083 --> 09:52.052
Not as meaningless as a jar
full of teeth. (screams)

09:52.086 --> 09:53.521
